    <div class="calc-layout">
      <div class="calc-main">
        <h1>😴 Sleep Calculator</h1>
        <p class="calc-intro">Find the best time to wake up or go to sleep based on your natural sleep cycles.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <label>What do you want to calculate?</label>
          <select id="sue-modo" onchange="toggleSleep()">
            <option value="despertar">I'm going to sleep now → what time should I wake up?</option>
            <option value="acostar">I want to wake up at → what time should I go to sleep?</option>
          </select>

          <div id="sue-hora-wrap">
            <label id="sue-hora-label">Time you are going to sleep</label>
            <input type="time" id="sue-hora" oninput="calcSleep()" style="width:100%;padding:0.65rem 0.9rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;font-size:1rem;background:var(--bg);margin-bottom:1rem">
          </div>

          <div class="result-box" id="sue-res">Enter the time</div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:2rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">
          <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem">How does this sleep calculator work?</h2>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Sleep is organised in cycles of approximately 90 minutes each. Each cycle includes light sleep, deep sleep and REM sleep stages. Waking up at the end of a complete cycle — during light sleep — makes you feel much more refreshed than waking up in the middle of deep sleep, even if you slept fewer hours total.</p>
          <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8">This calculator adds 15 minutes to account for the average time it takes to fall asleep. Most adults need 5 to 6 complete cycles (7.5 to 9 hours) per night for optimal rest.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is a sleep cycle?</h2>
          <p>A sleep cycle lasts approximately 90 minutes and includes four stages — light sleep, deeper sleep, deep sleep (slow wave) and REM sleep. REM sleep is when most dreaming occurs and is crucial for memory consolidation and emotional regulation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How many hours of sleep do I need?</summary>
            <p>Most adults need 7–9 hours per night (5–6 sleep cycles). Teenagers need 8–10 hours. Children need more. Quality matters as much as quantity.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What time should I go to sleep to wake up at 7am?</summary>
            <p>To wake up at 7:00 AM feeling refreshed, the ideal bedtimes are 9:45 PM (6 cycles), 11:15 PM (5 cycles), 12:45 AM (4 cycles) or 2:15 AM (3 cycles).</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Why do I feel groggy even after 8 hours of sleep?</summary>
            <p>Probably because your alarm woke you up in the middle of a deep sleep cycle. Try adjusting your wake-up time by 15–30 minutes to land at the end of a cycle.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
